Case-Based, Probabilistic Methods

Explanation: 
- Case-Based: The title of the paper explicitly mentions "Case-Based" and the abstract mentions the use of "novel case-based reasoning systems" in the original study by Naval Air Warfare Center (NAWC). The paper also discusses the replication and extension of the NAWC study using various case-based classifiers from the machine learning literature.
- Probabilistic Methods: Although not as prominent as the case-based approach, the paper does mention the testing of "several other classifiers (i.e., both case-based and otherwise) from the machine learning literature." This suggests the use of probabilistic methods, which are commonly used in many machine learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses the incorporation of "additional domain-specific knowledge" when applying case-based classifiers, which could involve the use of probabilistic models to represent uncertainty or probability distributions.
